      • adStart

        void adStart(int streamType,
             int playerType,
             int adPosition)
        Inform the session that an ad playback started.
        Parameters:
        streamType - The ad stream type. Either SdkConsts.AD_EMBEDDED if the ad is embedded into the content or SdkConsts.AD_SEPARATE if the ad is played separate from the main content.
        playerType - The ad player type. Either SdkConsts.AD_EMBEDDED if the ad is using the same player as the main content or SdkConsts.AD_SEPARATE if the ad is played in a separate player.
        adPosition - The ad position. One of SdkConsts.AD_POSITION_PREROLL, SdkConsts.AD_POSITION_MIDROLL, or SdkConsts.AD_POSITION_POSTROLL

      • seekProcessed

      • detachFromController

        boolean detachFromController()
        Detach the Analytics session from the PlayerController. Unregister listeners and remove any references.

        This method allows to unbind the AnalyticsSession from a PlayerController, to later set it to a new controller and continue with the same analytics session.

        Should be called by client code after getting the AnalyticsSession via PlayerController.getAnalyticsSession() , and before releasing the PlayerController.

        You can later re-attach the AnalyticsSession to a PlayerController before opening it with the PlayerController.setAnalyticsSession(AnalyticsSession) method

        NOTE: Note that the internal implementation relies on a proxy that wraps one or more AnalyticsSessions, for different analytics providers. This method will return true if and only if all of the underlying analytics session allow player controller detaching.

        Returns:
        whether this AnalyticsSession is successfully detached from the current PlayerController
